In such uses tantus and tantulus differ slightly from mag- nus and parvum they are more emphatic. — acini vinaceo: ⁸ a grapestone ’. — minutissimis: used here for minimis. Strictly speaking minutus ought to be used of things which are fragments of larger things, minutus being really the ,participle passive of minuo. In a well-known passage (Orat. 94) Cic. himself calls attention to the theoretical incorrectness of the use, which, however, is found through· out Latin literature.
